# Web Application Firewall (WAF)

A simple Web Application Firewall (WAF) to protect against SQL Injection, Cross-Site Scripting (XSS), Command Injection, and Directory Traversal attacks.

## Features
- Blocks SQL Injection
- Blocks Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)
- Blocks Command Injection
- Blocks Directory Traversal
- Logging and reporting

## Requirements
- Python 3.x
- Flask

## Installation
1. Clone the repository:
    ```bash
    git clone https://github.com/your-username/web-application-firewall.git
    cd web-application-firewall
    ```

2. Install the dependencies:
    ```bash
    pip install -r requirements.txt
    ```

## Usage
1. Run the application:
    ```bash
    python app.py
    ```

2. Access the web application in your browser:
    ```
    http://127.0.0.1:5000/
    ```

## Running Tests
1. Install the test dependencies (if any):
    ```bash
    pip install unittest
    ```

2. Run the tests:
    ```bash
    python -m unittest discover tests
    ```

## Example Endpoints
- Root URL:
    ```
    http://127.0.0.1:5000/
    ```

- Search Endpoint:
    ```
    http://127.0.0.1:5000/search?q=test
    ```

- Submit Endpoint:
    ```bash
    curl -X POST -d "data=test" http://127.0.0.1:5000/submit
    ```

